Until wave 17 the Feature toggle 'CONTEXTUAL_FORMATTING_IMPROVEMENTS' was turned off. Since that wave the toggle is on.

With that came a change in UI, that the 'Planning Enabled' checkbox was moved from Formatting Panel to Builder Panel.

For Application Design we explicitly suppressed the checkbox, as we do not support planning yet. It will be enabled in the near future with its own feature toggle.

Unfortunately the checks that were build in to prevent the checkbox from showing up in App Design are obsolete as soon as the Feature toggle 'CONTEXTUAL_FORMATTING_IMPROVEMENTS'  is turned on.

Original check is done in 

Table.controller.js â Line 13873 in function _updateFormattingPanel

            if (oDataRegion && oDataRegion.isInitialized() && !FT_CONTEXTUAL_FORMATTING_IMPROVEMENTS) {
                const bIsPlanningModel = oDataRegion && oDataRegion.getCubeProviderCached() && oDataRegion.getCubeProviderCached().getPlanningModel();
                const bIsAppInDesignMode = isAppBuildingView && TableSelectors._isDesignMode(this.getDocumentState(), this.getLocalStateForSelector());
                // enable Planning checkbox for all stories and all analytic apps in design mode
                if (bIsPlanningModel && (!isAppBuildingView || (FeatureToggle.isActive("APP_DESIGN_PLANNING") && bIsAppInDesignMode))) {
                    oFormattingPanel.showPlanningAsExplicitStepCheckBox(true);
                    oFormattingPanel.updatePlanningAsExplicitStepCheckBox(!!oDataRegion.getPlanningAsExplicitStepEnabled());
                } else {
                    oFormattingPanel.showPlanningAsExplicitStepCheckBox(false);
                    oFormattingPanel.updatePlanningAsExplicitStepCheckBox(false);
                }
            }

The desired behaviour from App Design point of view also needs to be ensured with Feature Toggle 'CONTEXTUAL_FORMATTING_IMPROVEMENTS' turned on
